<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" version="2.0"><channel><title>Personal Combined Feed</title><link>https://example.invalid</link><description>Personal aggregate feed</description><docs>http://www.rssboard.org/rss-specification</docs><generator>python-feedgen</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 21:19:34 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Show HN: Mneme – Open-protocol AI memory that lives on your device</title><link>https://github.com/ppserapiao/mneme</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Hey guys, so I use AI a lot, and I mean a lot, specially for my job and just as a hobby, I've got ADHD so creating is somethign I love, but I always got annoyed that every AI memory product wants to host my data on their servers, in their schema, locked to their product. Sooooo I built mneme memory that lives on your device, encrypted with keys only you hold, with an open protocol that works across Claude,Cursor, ChatGPT, Gemini.&lt;p&gt;Apache 2.0, on npm.&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/ppserapiao/mneme" rel="nofollow"&gt;https://github.com/ppserapiao/mneme&lt;/a&gt; · &lt;a href="https://mneme-web-zeta.vercel.app" rel="nofollow"&gt;https://mneme-web-zeta.vercel.app&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;Let me know your thoughts ;)&lt;/p&gt;
