&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 0&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48240859</guid><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 20:02:37 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>ASK HN: AI was always a probability problem?</title><link>https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48240840</link><description>&lt;p&gt;AI was always a probability problem.. If we look at the emergence of sequence models (or statistical learning in broader sense), they predict the next sequence based on the accumulation of knowledge that humankind has acquired over the years.. The scientists who were tackling this problem(creating general AI) before thought of approaching it by creating different simulations for all kinds of problems, which would have led to infinity anyway, that is why it never worked. The solution was simple. Wdyt?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Comments URL: &lt;a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48240840"&gt;https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48240840&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Points: 1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 2&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48240840</guid><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 20:01:35 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Ask HN: How to get involved and meet people in AI in SF?</title><link>https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48240777</link><description>&lt;p&gt;I'm a recently laid-off engineer, I've been playing around with AI to create apps, (vibe and not-vibe coding), and am blown away with how productive I can be. It feels like that feeling when I was in High School and built my first website and felt like I could build anything.&lt;p&gt;I live in San Francisco and have a bit of time before I start looking for a new job, but I realize I'm right in the heart of where all of this stuff is coming from.&lt;p&gt;How would you recommend I get involved/meet people doing cool things? Anything from groups that get together to someone who wants to grab a beer once a week and start a group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
